			<name>Paraguaná Refinery Complex</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Venezuela’s main refining hub<br></div><li>It’s <b>one of the largest refinery complexes in the world</b> (≈940–955 kb/d capacity)<br></li><li>It represents <b>~70% of Venezuela’s refining capacity</b><br></li><li><br></li><li>🏢 Owner: <span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">PDVSA</span></span><br></li><li>⚙️ Capacity: <b>~940,000 bpd</b><br></li><li>🧪 Specialisation: Heavy crude upgrading (flexicoking)<br></li><li>📏 Scale: Multi-refinery complex (Amuay + Cardón)<b></b><br></li><div><br></div><p>Includes multiple sites:<br></p><ul><li>Amuay refinery<br></li><li>Cardón refinery<br></li><li>Bajo Grande refinery<br></li></ul><div><br></div>]]></description>
