		<Placemark id="09C8EF4BC13EB8B1E0B0">
			<name>ExxonMobil Rotterdam Refinery</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<h1>⚙️ What this refinery is<br></h1><ul><li>A <b>major European refinery</b> operated by <span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">ExxonMobil</span></span><br></li><li>Part of a <b>large integrated site</b> (refinery + petrochemicals)<br></li></ul><p>👉 It produces:<br></p><ul><li>Gasoline<br></li><li>Diesel (ULSD)<br></li><li>Jet fuel<br></li><li>Base oils<br></li><li>Petrochemical feedstocks<br></li></ul><div><hr><br></div><h1>🔗 Why it’s important<br></h1><p>Rotterdam is one of the <b>biggest refining hubs in the world</b>, and ExxonMobil is one of several major players there:<br></p><ul><li>Shell (Pernis refinery — largest in Europe)<br></li><li>BP refinery<br></li><li>ExxonMobil refinery<br></li></ul><p>👉 Crude oil arrives by tanker, then:<br></p><ul><li>Gets refined in Rotterdam<br></li><li><div>Sent to:<br></div><ul><li>Antwerp (chemicals)<br></li><li>Amsterdam (storage/trading)<br></li><li>Inland Europe via pipelines<br></li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div>]]></description>
