			<description><![CDATA[<h1><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">BP Gelsenkirchen</span></span> refinery complex<br></h1><p>Historically also called:<br></p><ul><li>Ruhr Oel<br></li><li>Ruhr Oel GmbH<br></li><li>BP Ruhr Oel<br></li></ul><p>It is one of the largest refining and petrochemical complexes in Germany.<br></p><div><hr><br></div><h1>What you are seeing on your image<br></h1><p>Your screenshot shows:<br></p><ul><li>tank farms<br></li><li>refining units<br></li><li>petrochemical installations<br></li><li>canals/logistics infrastructure<br></li></ul><p>The refinery complex is split mainly between:<br></p><ul><li>Scholven<br></li><li>Horst<br></li></ul><p>inside the Ruhr industrial region.<br></p><div><hr><br></div><h1>Why Gelsenkirchen is strategically important<br></h1><p>This refinery sits at the heart of:<br></p><ul><li>the Ruhr industrial basin<br></li><li>German fuel demand<br></li><li>petrochemical consumption<br></li><li>pipeline logistics<br></li></ul><p>It receives crude through major systems connected to:<br></p><ul><li><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Rotterdam</span></span><br></li><li>North Sea imports<br></li><li>inland German pipeline networks<br></li></ul><div><hr><br></div><h1>Main products produced there<br></h1><p>The refinery produces:<br></p><ul><li>gasoline<br></li><li>diesel<br></li><li>jet fuel<br></li><li>heating oil<br></li><li>petrochemical feedstocks<br></li></ul><p>Capacity is roughly:<br></p><ul><li>12 million tonnes/year<br></li><li>~265,000 barrels/day processing capacity<br></li></ul><div><hr><br></div><h1>Why the canals matter<br></h1><p>Notice the waterways on your image.<br></p><p>The refinery is connected to:<br></p><ul><li>the Rhine-Ruhr inland waterway system<br></li><li>barge logistics<br></li><li>chemical transport corridors<br></li></ul><p>This is EXTREMELY important in Northwest European oil trading.<br></p><h1>Very important trading insight<br></h1><p>The Ruhr region is one of Europe’s largest:<br></p><ul><li>diesel demand centers<br></li><li>petrochemical clusters<br></li><li>industrial fuel markets<br></li></ul><p>That is why pipelines from <span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Rotterdam</span></span> toward the Ruhr are so critical.<br></p><p>The logic is basically:<br></p><pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><br></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼs ͼ16"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>Rotterdam imports</span><br><span>       ↓</span><br><span>Pipeline system</span><br><span>       ↓</span><br><span>Ruhr refineries</span><br><span>       ↓</span><br><span>German industry &amp; consumers</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div><br></div></div></div></div></div></pre><div><hr><br></div><h1>Interesting current development<br></h1><p>BP recently agreed to sell the refinery to the Klesch Group as part of its portfolio simplification strategy.<br></p><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>7.049740606944428</longitude>
				<latitude>51.54405453015391</latitude>
				<altitude>30.32855574917301</altitude>
				<heading>0</heading>
				<tilt>0</tilt>
				<gx:fovy>35</gx:fovy>
				<range>7933.802029959625</range>
				<altitudeMode>absolute</altitudeMode>
			</LookAt>
			<styleUrl>#msn_icon?color=8d6e63&amp;id=2000&amp;scale=40</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>7.047603258144561,51.53819523473279,28.58942788441671</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="0F229C480B3FCC0E95ED">
			<name>VAROPreem - VARO Refining Cressier SA</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Cressier is Switzerland’s only conventional fuel manufacturing facility. It supplies approximately 30% of the national fuel market and is critical infrastructure for national supply. In 2023, together with Groupe E, VARO commissioned Switzerland’s most powerful ground-mounted solar farm (7.7 MW), capable of providing up to 60% of the refinery’selectricity at peak, and started supplying residual heat to a local district heating network, warming over 5,000 nearby households<br></div><div><br></div><div>Strategic importance: Monopoly-like position as Switzerland’s sole refinery gives pricing power and strategic value. A captive domestic market (Switzerland is landlocked, reducing import competition) means more stable margins. The solar integration and district heating make it a showcase for VARO’s “decarbonise while operating” philosophy.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>7.033661299999999</longitude>
				<latitude>47.0400065</latitude>
