		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="0ABF44347B3FDB9E58EA">
			<name>Gunvor Petroleum Rotterdam refinery</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 20px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 20px;">It is the </span></span></span><span style="font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><b><span class="font" style="font-family: TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 20px;">Gunvor Energy Rotterdam (GER)</span></span></b></span><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 20px;"> refinery site, where the new SAF/HVO plant is being built on a brownfield section of the refinery. VARO and Gunvor explicitly state that the SAF facility will be located at the Gunvor Energy Rotterdam site.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><br></p><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>The site includes:<br></div><div><br></div><div>* Crude oil refinery (~75 kbpd)<br></div><div>* Tank farms<br></div><div>* Marine jetties<br></div><div>* Pipeline connections to the Rotterdam refining and storage network<br></div><div>* The future VARO/Gunvor SAF-HVO facility under development&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></div><div><br></div><div>Why this location is strategically important<br></div><div><br></div><div>For your energy-trading interviews, this is worth understanding:<br></div><div><br></div><div>1. Crude arrives by tanker into Europoort.<br></div><div>2. The refinery is connected to the wider Rotterdam pipeline system.<br></div><div>3. Jet fuel and SAF can move toward airports, including Amsterdam Airport Schiphol.<br></div><div>4. Existing tanks, utilities, docks, and pipelines dramatically reduce the cost of building the SAF plant.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
