		<Placemark id="0B1B82F80D3ED2D647F7">
			<name>Toward Secunda (major industrial hub)</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>One of the biggest <b>fuel and petrochemical centers</b> in Africa<br></div><div>It is mainly a <b>coal-to-liquids (CTL) and gas-to-liquids (GTL) plant</b>, plus petrochemicals.<br></div><div><br></div><h2>🔹 What’s the difference from a refinery?<br></h2><h3>Traditional refinery:<br></h3><ul><li>Input: <b>crude oil</b><br></li><li>Process: distillation + cracking<br></li><li>Output: petrol, diesel, LPG, etc.<br></li></ul><div><hr><br></div><h3>Secunda (Sasol complex):<br></h3><ul><li><div>Input:<br></div><ul><li><b>Coal</b> (mainly)<br></li><li>Natural gas (partly)<br></li></ul></li><li><div>Process:<br></div><ul><li>Convert coal → synthetic fuel (via chemical processes)<br></li></ul></li><li><div>Output:<br></div><ul><li>Petrol, diesel<br></li><li>Chemicals, plastics<br></li></ul></li></ul><h2>Why Secunda matters in your pipeline discussion<br></h2><p>Even though it’s not a refinery:<br></p><p>👉 It is a <b>major fuel and petrochemical demand center</b><br></p><p>So fuel coming from Mozambique can:<br></p><ul><li><div>Supply:<br></div><ul><li>Industry<br></li><li>Transport fuels<br></li></ul></li><li>Complement local production<br></li></ul><div><hr><br></div><h2>🔹 Key idea<br></h2><ul><li>Refinery = processes crude oil<br></li><li>Secunda = <b>manufactures fuels chemically from coal/gas</b><br></li></ul><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>29.18180103852775</longitude>
				<latitude>-26.55649899402862</latitude>
				<altitude>1604.534677316579</altitude>
				<heading>0</heading>
				<tilt>0</tilt>
				<gx:fovy>35</gx:fovy>
				<range>13651.86412865064</range>
				<altitudeMode>absolute</altitudeMode>
			</LookAt>
