			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="06D7DDADB63F32DB299F">
			<name>Mont Belvieu, Texas</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>Mont Belvieu, Texas is the largest natural gas liquids (NGL) and liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) storage and fractionation hub in North America, and one of the most important hydrocarbon trading hubs in the global energy system.<br></p><p>Located east of Houston along the Texas Gulf Coast, the Mont Belvieu hub developed around the Barbers Hill salt dome, a naturally occurring underground salt formation ideally suited for the creation of massive hydrocarbon storage caverns. These underground caverns store propane, butane, ethane, iso-butane, natural gasoline, and mixed NGL streams delivered from producing basins across the United States.<br></p><p>The hub functions as the primary pricing and logistics center for US LPG and NGL markets. “Mt. Belvieu” is widely used in global energy trading as a benchmark price reference for propane and butane, similar to Henry Hub for natural gas or Cushing for crude oil. Physical spot prices, futures contracts, swaps, and international LPG cargo pricing are all closely linked to Mont Belvieu assessments.<br></p><p>The industrial complex includes:<br></p><ul><li><p>Extensive underground salt-cavern storage systems<br></p></li><li><p>Large-scale NGL fractionation plants<br></p></li><li><p>Pipeline interconnections from the Permian Basin, Eagle Ford, Bakken, and Marcellus regions<br></p></li><li><p>LPG export infrastructure connected to the Houston Ship Channel<br></p></li><li><p>Petrochemical feedstock distribution networks<br></p></li></ul><p>Mixed NGL streams (“Y-grade”) arriving at Mont Belvieu are processed through fractionation towers where hydrocarbons are separated into purity products such as ethane, propane, normal butane, iso-butane, and natural gasoline. These products are then stored, traded, exported, or supplied to petrochemical plants and refineries.<br></p><p>The Mont Belvieu hub contains hundreds of millions of barrels of underground storage capacity and several million barrels per day of fractionation capability, making it one of the largest hydrocarbon processing and storage systems ever built.<br></p><p>Today, Mont Belvieu serves as the central balancing point for US NGL production and the dominant export supply hub for propane and butane shipments to Asia, Europe, and Latin America. The growth of US shale production transformed Mont Belvieu from a regional LPG center into a globally significant energy trading benchmark and export platform.<br></p><div><br></div>]]></description>
