		<Placemark id="02F63AE6E93FCA0C0978">
			<name>Port of Moerdijk</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 20px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><span class="size" style="font-size:20px">It is located about </span></span></span><span style="font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><b><span class="font" style="font-family:TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT"><span class="size" style="font-size:20px">35–40 km south of Rotterdam</span></span></b></span><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><span class="size" style="font-size:20px">, on the southern shore of the </span></span></span><span style="font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><b><span class="font" style="font-family:TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT"><span class="size" style="font-size:20px">Hollands Diep</span></span></b></span><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><span class="size" style="font-size:20px"> estuary, between the towns of </span></span></span><span style="font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><b><span class="font" style="font-family:TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT"><span class="size" style="font-size:20px">Moerdijk</span></span></b></span><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><span class="size" style="font-size:20px">, </span></span></span><span style="font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><b><span class="font" style="font-family:TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT"><span class="size" style="font-size:20px">Zevenbergen</span></span></b></span><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><span class="size" style="font-size:20px">, and </span></span></span><span style="font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><b><span class="font" style="font-family:TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT"><span class="size" style="font-size:20px">Klundert</span></span></b></span><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><span class="size" style="font-size:20px">. The labels visible on your screenshot (Strijensas, Zevenbergen, A17, Roode Vaart, Hollands Diep) confirm the location.<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><br></p><div><br></div><div>What are you looking at?<br></div><div><br></div><div>The large industrial zone in the lower half of the image is the Port of Moerdijk, one of the Netherlands’ major industrial and logistics hubs. It is:<br></div><div><br></div><div>* The 4th seaport of the Netherlands.<br></div><div>* A major chemical and petrochemical cluster.<br></div><div>* Connected by pipeline, rail, barge, road, and sea transport.<br></div><div>* Strategically positioned between the ports of Rotterdam and Antwerp.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></div><div><br></div><div>Why is it interesting for energy trading?<br></div><div><br></div><div>For someone trying to break into the energy industry, this area is extremely relevant because it hosts:<br></div><div><br></div><div>* Petrochemical plants<br></div><div>* Tank storage facilities<br></div><div>* Chemical manufacturers<br></div><div>* Logistics terminals<br></div><div>* Pipeline infrastructure linking Rotterdam, Antwerp, and Germany&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></div><div><br></div><div>Shell connection<br></div><div><br></div><div>This is also where ** Shell Netherlands￼** has a major petrochemical complex. In fact, Shell was the first major company to establish itself in Moerdijk in the late 1960s and opened its first factory there in 1973.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></div><div><br></div><div>If you’re studying energy trading<br></div><div><br></div><div>The interesting thing is that this area contains exactly the type of assets traders care about:<br></div><div><br></div><div>* Storage tanks<br></div><div>* Chemical plants<br></div><div>* Feedstock consumers<br></div><div>* Barge terminals<br></div><div>* Pipeline connections<br></div><div>* Inland shipping infrastructure<br></div><div><br></div><div>When traders talk about physical flows of naphtha, LPG, chemicals, biofuels, methanol, ammonia, etc., Moerdijk is one of the places where those molecules are actually moving.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>4.6062531</longitude>
				<latitude>51.6745104</latitude>
				<altitude>0</altitude>
				<heading>0</heading>
				<tilt>0</tilt>
				<gx:fovy>35</gx:fovy>
				<range>1476.039435460105</range>
				<altitudeMode>relativeToGround</altitudeMode>
			</LookAt>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0A987091184081E89020</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<altitudeMode>relativeToGround</altitudeMode>
				<coordinates>4.6063798,51.6745618,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
