			<styleUrl>#msn_icon?color=000000&amp;id=2000&amp;scale=4</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>104.169107161563,1.358405746407063,5.486147625727451</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="00C02568723EB7B9A5C6">
			<name>MOL Petrochemicals Tiszaújváros</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<div><div>What it does:&nbsp;Uses <b>refinery outputs (like naphtha, propylene)</b><br></div></div><li><div>Turns them into : plastics,&nbsp;industrial chemicals<br></div></li><div><br></div><div>Produces:<br></div><ul><li><ul><li>plastics (polyethylene, polypropylene)<br></li><li>synthetic rubber<br></li><li>chemical intermediates (polyols, propylene, etc.)<br></li></ul></li><li>Part of <b><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">MOL Group</span></span></b><br></li></ul><p>👉 It’s one of MOL’s <b>two main chemical production sites in Hungary</b><br></p><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>21.0491307468206</longitude>
				<latitude>47.89381560823652</latitude>
				<altitude>91.84558328701513</altitude>
				<heading>0</heading>
				<tilt>0</tilt>
				<gx:fovy>35</gx:fovy>
				<range>6673.615556481527</range>
				<altitudeMode>absolute</altitudeMode>
			</LookAt>
			<styleUrl>#msn_icon?color=000000&amp;id=2000&amp;scale=4</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>21.02832293073626,47.89420784451342,93.98698311388492</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="0C008C1AB53EB8584258">
			<name>Dow Terneuzen</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<h1>🧪 What it is<br></h1><ul><li>Operated by: <span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Dow</span></span><br></li><li><div>Often referred to as:<br></div><ul><li><b>Dow Terneuzen</b><br></li><li><b>Dow Benelux site</b><br></li></ul></li></ul><p>👉 It’s one of <b>Dow’s largest production sites outside the US</b><br></p><div><hr><br></div><h1>⚙️ What happens there<br></h1><p>It’s a <b>fully integrated petrochemical complex</b>, producing:<br></p><ul><li>Plastics (polyethylene, polystyrene)<br></li><li>Chemical intermediates<br></li><li>Industrial materials<br></li></ul><p>👉 Think:<br></p><blockquote><p>Raw hydrocarbons → chemicals → plastics → industrial products<br></p></blockquote><div><hr><br></div><h1>🌍 Why it’s so big<br></h1><ul><li>Located inside <b><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">North Sea Port</span></span></b><br></li><li><div>Connected to:<br></div><ul><li>Antwerp petrochemical cluster<br></li><li>Rotterdam refining hub<br></li></ul></li><li><div>Access to:<br></div><ul><li>Ships (via canal)<br></li><li>Pipelines<br></li><li>European markets<br></li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>3.787764908666296</longitude>
				<latitude>51.34081760073316</latitude>
				<altitude>3.924655696200103</altitude>
				<heading>0</heading>
				<tilt>0</tilt>
				<gx:fovy>35</gx:fovy>
				<range>7707.195568123134</range>
				<altitudeMode>absolute</altitudeMode>
			</LookAt>
			<styleUrl>#msn_icon?color=000000&amp;id=2000&amp;scale=4</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>3.786962797359981,51.34445943366449,3.911769979405457</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="05EE12FD073EB86434EF">
			<name>BASF Antwerp</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>One of the largest chemical sites in Europe :<br></div><div><br></div><div>BASF Antwerp is one of the largest integrated petrochemical complexes in Europe, operated by <b><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">BASF</span></span></b>. It functions as a <b>“Verbund” site</b>, meaning that multiple production units are physically and operationally interconnected to maximize efficiency.<br></div><p>At the core of the site is a <b>steam cracker</b>, which converts hydrocarbon feedstocks (mainly naphtha) into basic petrochemicals such as ethylene and propylene. These molecules are then processed on-site into a wide range of intermediate and specialty chemicals, including plastics, performance materials, coatings, and industrial inputs.<br></p><p>A defining feature of BASF Antwerp is its <b>high level of internal integration</b>: by-products from one process are reused as inputs for another, minimizing waste and reducing costs. The site is designed to handle the full value chain—from basic chemicals to higher-value finished products—within a single industrial ecosystem.<br></p><h2>🔑 Key characteristics<br></h2><ul><li>Fully integrated <b>end-to-end chemical production site</b><br></li><li>Produces both <b>base chemicals and high-value downstream products</b><br></li><li>Strong internal reuse of materials and energy (Verbund system)<br></li><li>Highly complex and diversified production structure<br></li></ul>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>4.27482130396456</longitude>
				<latitude>51.36300578009773</latitude>
				<altitude>6.864890533245029</altitude>
				<heading>0</heading>
				<tilt>0</tilt>
				<gx:fovy>35</gx:fovy>
				<range>4850.543096734327</range>
				<altitudeMode>absolute</altitudeMode>
			</LookAt>
			<styleUrl>#msn_icon?color=000000&amp;id=2000&amp;scale=4</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>4.267771448412327,51.36534927375749,19.10874670620181</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="0467A13A993EB8752C2C">
			<name>INEOS Antwerp</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>INEOS Antwerp is a major petrochemical production site operated by <b><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">INEOS</span></span></b>, specializing in the manufacture of <b>core petrochemical building blocks</b>. The site focuses primarily on the production of olefins such as ethylene and propylene, as well as polymers and intermediate chemical products.<br></p><p>Unlike fully integrated complexes, INEOS Antwerp follows a more <b>specialized production model</b>, concentrating on large-scale, efficient output of key chemical intermediates. These products are then supplied via pipelines and logistics networks to other industrial sites—both within the Antwerp cluster and across Europe—including companies like BASF.<br></p><p>The site is tightly integrated into the wider Antwerp petrochemical network, with extensive pipeline connections to refineries and neighboring chemical plants. This allows INEOS to operate as a <b>critical supplier of feedstocks</b> within a highly interconnected industrial ecosystem.<br></p><h2>🔑 Key characteristics<br></h2><ul><li>Focus on <b>core petrochemical production (olefins, polymers)</b><br></li><li>Large-scale, <b>high-efficiency steam cracking operations</b><br></li><li>Supplies intermediates to other chemical producers<br></li><li>Strong integration into regional pipeline and industrial networks<br></li></ul><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>4.273925657437596</longitude>
				<latitude>51.36379448949879</latitude>
				<altitude>5.888479591567424</altitude>
				<heading>0</heading>
				<tilt>0</tilt>
				<gx:fovy>35</gx:fovy>
				<range>6042.380869329209</range>
				<altitudeMode>absolute</altitudeMode>
			</LookAt>
			<styleUrl>#msn_icon?color=000000&amp;id=2000&amp;scale=4</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>4.262152203735479,51.36047499017207,7.21164629532076</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
	</Folder>
	<Folder>
		<name>Strategic Transport Infrastructure</name>
		<Placemark id="08208D690D3E474BF1D3">
