		<Placemark id="09BE71D1E53F2D4290A0">
			<name>Kurdistan export pipeline</name>
			<description>Status : Operational, subject to political and commercial disruptions.

The Kurdistan Export Pipeline is a crude oil pipeline located mainly within the Kurdistan Region of Iraq. It collects oil from Kurdish producing areas, including the Taq Taq and Khurmala systems, and transports it northwest to Fish Khabur at the Iraq–Türkiye border. At Fish Khabur, the pipeline connects with the Turkish section of the Iraq–Turkey Pipeline, which carries the crude onward to the Ceyhan export terminal.

Operational status: Operational as part of the current export route.

Exports of crude from northern Iraq and the Kurdistan Region through Türkiye resumed after the prolonged suspension that began in March 2023. The regional pipeline therefore currently provides the Iraqi connection to the operating Turkish export corridor, although flows remain exposed to commercial, political and security interruptions.</description>
