				</coordinates>
			</LineString>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Abu Dhabi Crude Oil Pipeline</name>
			<description>The Abu Dhabi Crude Oil Pipeline, also known as the Habshan–Fujairah Pipeline or ADCOP, transports crude oil from the Habshan production and collection hub in Abu Dhabi to storage and offshore loading facilities at Fujairah on the Gulf of Oman. By reaching a port located outside the Persian Gulf, the pipeline allows UAE crude exports to bypass the Strait of Hormuz. The approximately 380-kilometre pipeline is operational and has a capacity of around 1.5–1.8 million barrels per day.</description>
